00:35:38,660 --> 00:35:41,500
♫ <i> Layer after layer, </i> ♫

396
00:35:41,500 --> 00:35:50,280
♫ <i>it turns into an eternity</i> ♫

397
00:36:36,000 --> 00:36:38,500
Shiba, just go.

398
00:36:40,439 --> 00:36:42,320
Stand up.

399
00:36:43,940 --> 00:36:47,660
No matter what General Luo said, it won't work.

400
00:36:47,660 --> 00:36:50,079
You don't need to regard me as your master. You—

401
00:36:50,080 --> 00:36:53,738
Yanyun Cavalrymen's rule, after following one master, we'll die rather than betray.

402
00:36:53,738 --> 00:36:55,159
You can talk?

403
00:36:55,159 --> 00:36:56,659
I can.

404
00:36:56,659 --> 00:36:58,920
Then, why didn't you talk before?

405
00:36:58,920 --> 00:37:01,099
Because it was not necessary.

406
00:37:02,579 --> 00:37:06,839
In all, you don't need to regard anyone as your master now.

407
00:37:06,840 --> 00:37:07,958
You can leave now.

408
00:37:07,959 --> 00:37:10,738
Leave? Where can I go?

409
00:37:10,738 --> 00:37:12,720
You can go wherever you want.

410
00:37:12,720 --> 00:37:14,759
Do whatever you want to do.

411
00:37:14,759 --> 00:37:16,039
You're free now.

412
00:37:16,040 --> 00:37:18,579
No one can restrain you now.

413
00:37:18,579 --> 00:37:20,179
Free?

414
00:37:23,479 --> 00:37:25,079
Go!

415
00:37:34,120 --> 00:37:35,900
Why are you here?

416
00:37:35,900 --> 00:37:37,739
Are you afraid I won't leave?

417
00:37:37,739 --> 00:37:41,159
According to Sun, he is afraid of this.

418
00:37:42,760 --> 00:37:44,279
Did you see the letter?

419
00:37:44,280 --> 00:37:45,980
What?

420
00:37:45,980 --> 00:37:48,319
Where did you get that letter?

421
00:37:48,320 --> 00:37:50,620
It's from Khan's tent. There's some pigeon blood on it.

422
00:37:50,620 --> 00:37:52,279
It means it's urgent.

423
00:37:52,279 --> 00:37:56,199
I didn't see the letter. But there's something in it.

424
00:37:57,399 --> 00:37:59,239
I saw it.

425
00:38:02,959 --> 00:38:04,740
It's a pair of earrings.

426
00:38:04,740 --> 00:38:07,119
Earrings?

427
00:38:07,119 --> 00:38:11,299
Is any woman related to Sun in Khan's tent?

428
00:38:11,299 --> 00:38:13,780
- His mother!
- His mother?

429
00:38:13,780 --> 00:38:16,520
Isn't he an orphan?

430
00:38:16,520 --> 00:38:18,979
She's his foster mother, called A'Yi'er.

431
00:38:18,979 --> 00:38:22,799
If A'Yi'er didn't pick him and bring him up when he was young,

432
00:38:22,800 --> 00:38:24,759
he would have died.

433
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:29,200
For all these years, Great Khan has been asking A'Yi'er to work in his tent.

434
00:38:29,200 --> 00:38:31,159
He wants Sun to be loyal to him.

435
00:38:31,159 --> 00:38:34,120
No wonder Sun listens to Great Khan.

436
00:38:34,120 --> 00:38:36,800
It's because of A'Yi'er.

437
00:38:41,080 --> 00:38:44,339
- Where're you going?
- Mu Jin, it's a trap.

438
00:38:44,339 --> 00:38:48,059
If Sun goes back alone, he'll be in danger.

439
00:38:48,800 --> 00:38:52,019
Now, something must have happened to A'Yi'er.

440
00:38:52,019 --> 00:38:53,940
Let's go quickly!

441
00:38:56,399 --> 00:38:57,559
Why are you here?

442
00:38:57,560 --> 00:38:59,298
You said it. I can go wherever I want.

443
00:38:59,298 --> 00:39:01,420
I want to save A'Yi'er.

444
00:39:02,360 --> 00:39:05,960
Call Eagle Division. If we can't save her, we can just grab her.

445
00:39:32,140 --> 00:39:34,000
She'er!

446
00:39:42,600 --> 00:39:44,239
You're finally here.

447
00:39:44,239 --> 00:39:46,939
She'er, it's just something between us.

448
00:39:46,939 --> 00:39:48,678
Don't let innocent people get involved.

449
00:39:48,679 --> 00:39:50,179
Okay.

450
00:39:50,179 --> 00:39:52,660
As long as you kneel down and apologize to me,

451
00:39:52,660 --> 00:39:55,080
maybe I won't kill her.

452
00:40:06,560 --> 00:40:08,079
She'er, how dare you!

453
00:40:08,080 --> 00:40:10,059
Of course, I dare.

454
00:40:12,499 --> 00:40:14,959
Now her life is depending on you.

455
00:40:14,959 --> 00:40:17,420
Kneel or not, make your choice.

456
00:40:24,879 --> 00:40:27,439
It seems you need some help.

457
00:40:47,200 --> 00:40:48,659
You threaten me with a woman.

458
00:40:48,659 --> 00:40:51,278
She'er, you're a coward!

459
00:40:51,278 --> 00:40:52,438
You!

460
00:40:52,439 --> 00:40:55,860
If you're a real man, come and fight with me.

461
00:40:55,860 --> 00:40:58,140
Don't let me look down on you!

462
00:40:59,840 --> 00:41:03,840
General Sun, a wise man submits to fate.

463
00:41:03,840 --> 00:41:07,060
You're not qualified to negotiate with Young Khan now.

464
00:41:07,060 --> 00:41:08,900
Kneel or not?

465
00:42:25,900 --> 00:42:28,520
Let my mother go.

466
00:42:28,520 --> 00:42:31,799
Since you have kneeled down, what about having a kowtow?

467
00:42:31,800 --> 00:42:34,040
Entertain us.

468
00:42:39,020 --> 00:42:40,720
What?

469
00:42:40,720 --> 00:42:43,959
Your dignity is more important than your mother's life?

